A recent outbreak of the H5N1 strain of bird flu in Hong Kong has led to several deaths and cases of infection.
Hospitals and clinics are testing patients and their relatives for flu-like symptoms.
Local health officials are monitoring staff who had contact with victims.
Experts advise buying poultry only from licensed vendors to prevent the spread of the virus.
Macao residents are cautioned but not panicked over the situation.
Authorities are closely monitoring chicken diseases in neighboring provinces.
Despite the cases, there is no evidence of human-to-human transmission, and imported poultry is deemed safe for consumption.
